@node BESOIN "What do you need"
      Bomber Gug v1.0 works with :
      - An Amiga of course : from A500 to A4000.
      - Two pads or two joysticks.
      - At least 1 MO of memory
      - Bomber Gug (of course !!)
      - Some programs in C: : Endcli, Copy, Assign
      - Some libraries (I don't know them but I think there isn't any problem)
      - Workbench from version 2.0 (I think)
      - Asl.library

        Bomber Gug v1.0 have just been tested on an Amiga 1200 68030 28 Mhz with 4 MO
  of Fast memory , an Hard disk of 257 MO, a Cd-Rom x4,with the Workbench 3.0 with
  a screen 640x480 in Multiscan/Productivity in 32 colors.
@endnode
@node INSTALLATION "How to install the game on the hard disk ?"
      There are two ways for installing Bomber Gug v1.0 :
         - The easy way : use Install program.
           Run Install from the Workbench and follow all instructions on the screen.
         - The hard way : manual installation
           Drag all the files and drawers of the Bomber Gug drawer and drop them in
           the drawer in which you want to install BomBer Gug.If there is a problem
           of language, click @{"here" LINK LANGUE}.
      If after the installation the game doesn't work, check if you have all is
      @{"needed" LINK BESOIN}
@endnode
@node LANGUE "How to change the language of the game ?"
      If you want to change the language of the game without @{"reinstall" LINK INSTALLATION} it
   you must use Install_Langue program.How does it work ?
      - Double click on his icon (in the Workbench of course !)
      - A window will appear. 
      - There are just 2 languages : French and English.If you want more languages
        @{"contact me !" LINK CONTACT}
      - Choice your language with the numbers : 1 or 2
      - Deprotect your disk (if you have Bomber Gug on a disk)
      - Wait a few seconds.
      - Your language is installed.
   There is an another way : edit - if it exists - the file Langue, on the first line
   write Francais to have french in the game
         Anglais  to have english in the game
   Then save this file in Ascii.
@endnode
